On Tue, 28 May 2002, Mathew L. Nardone wrote:

> Hello. 
> I've been through the archive but didn't find any notes pertinent to my
> particular situation, so I'm asking for some diagnostic help.  I recently
> bought a '78 transporter, that at the time had a louder than normal exhaust.
> I left the exhaust initially, and did a tune up  - new wires, plugs,
> condensor, points, gapped it and set the timing. When I was done it idled
> fine, ran pretty well, but sounded like a dragster - the exhaust had already
> gotten louder in the two weeks I'd had it. A few days later, I started
> driving it to the mechanics, 8 miles away, to address the exhaust problem.
> The bus was coughing and sputtering until the muffler finally fell off. I
> tied it up, and coughed and sputtered the rest of the way to the mechanic.
> He replaced the heat exchangers (not sure of the make but the sticker says
> they're from Denmark) and said it was all set,  but running rough. I went to
> pick it up, and it would turn over and start up, but wouldn't hold an idle
> for more than 30 seconds and would choke whenever you stepped on the gas.
> You really have to work the gas pedal to keep it running. Driving it was out
> of the question. The mechanic has adopted the position - "I just worked on
> the exhaust, anything else is your problem", so I don't really have a great
> working relationship with him, though he's supposed to be the local VW
> mechanic.
> 
> Any thoughts or info is greatly appreciated.
